09/02/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The six NATO invitees will be full-fledged members of the Alliance in mid-March, with an official ceremony on 2 April, Bulgarian Defence Minister Nikolay Svinarov said Sunday (8 February). 
He added that Russia had voiced no objections to Bulgaria's entry into NATO or the possible relocation of US military bases to the country.
In other news, following a weekend meeting in Tehran, Bulgaria and Iran are working to boost co-operation in trade and the energy sector. 
The countries have decided to establish a joint committee on enhanced economic relations. 
(Trud, 24 Chassa - 09/02/04; BNT, BTA, BNR, IRIB - 08/02/04)
